    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse <strong>half <span class=\"text-danger\">[all]</span></strong> the <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 2? Save the remaining chickpeas for another recipe!</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped pepper </strong>and<strong> shallot wedges </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>with the <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and <strong>curry powder </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>creamed coconut </strong>and <strong>tamari soy sauce </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
